article.headline: Wildcats hold Spartans to 7 field goals in each half
article.linkText: Arizona smothers UNC Greensboro in easy win
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (Ticker) -- Dee-Dee Wheeler scored 19 points and No. 25 Arizona held UNC Greensboro to seven field goals in each half in an easy 98-48 victory for the Wildcats.

Wheeler hit 8-of-14 shots, including 2-of-3 from the arc, to pace five Wildcats in double figures. Natalie Jones scored 15 and Shawntinice Polk had 13 points and grabbed 10 rebounds.

Arizona (5-1) got 41 points off the bench as Ashley Whisonant had 16 and Katrina Linder added 11.

The Wildcats led 53-24 at the half as they limited the Spartans to 7-of-23 (30.4) shooting. Things got no easier in the second half for UNC-Greensboro, which shot 7-of-26 (26.9).

Kemena Brooks and Meghan Chamberlain each scored 10 points for the Spartans (1-3).
